@terryfetters8555 - "Plays to strengthen the presidency"??  Funny how all the goal lines moved drastically the moment he stepped into office. He does things that every other president in modern history has done with no questions... and gets sued for each and every move he makes.
    Every move he's made gets greeted with the media clutching pearls and running for the nearest fainting couch, pretending it's all "unprecedented" or "unconstitutional".  And many of these are  things they cheered for when Obama or Biden were in office. Yet now they are claiming these moves are "dictatorial". They hold "No kings" rallies, and throw tantrums over everything he accomplishes.
    It's political theater, and the unending lawsuits are mere stalling tactics. So lets stop pretending that Trump is somehow usurping new presidential powers or doing unprecedented actions. His effectiveness may be unprecedented in that he gets a LOT done... including things the DNC has spent the last 30 years promising to do, but failing. He makes them look bad. He's good at what he does, and they hate him for it. It shows how utterly incompetent most of them really are.
